# Retired routes. /pitch-index was the duplicate of the Pitch Index; the canonical
# directory now lives at /repertoire (rows default + a Cards view). 301 so any old
# link or crawl lands on the live page instead of the SPA 404.
/pitch-index   /repertoire  301
/pitch-index/  /repertoire  301
/classify      /repertoire  301
/classify/     /repertoire  301
/kinetic-chain /learn/mechanics 301
/kinetic-chain/ /learn/mechanics 301
/lost-pitches/smokey-joe-williams-velocity /lost-pitches/smokey-joe-williams-fastball 301
/lost-pitches/smokey-joe-williams-velocity/ /lost-pitches/smokey-joe-williams-fastball 301

# No SPA catch-all. Every real route is prerendered to its own HTML file and is
# served directly; anything else falls through to 404.html (the prerendered
# NotFound view, copied into place by the build) with a real 404 status. A 200
# app shell for unknown paths would tell crawlers every typo is a page.
